Encounter.title: First day of school
Encounter.Author: nobody
Encounter.IntroText: You’re sitting with your classmates at lunch. It is the second day of school and you already feel the overwhelming exhaustion of putting your best performance on. =AntagonistName= is sitting next to you, showing everyone her instagram photos from her trip to Italy this summer. Basically, 80 percent of the pictures are just her half naked in a bikini at the pool.. You turn your head and look around the room observing the interesting species of school kids. You notice how everyone seems unnaturally happy, sitting with their biggest smiles, best clothes, and pretending to have their time of their lives. Suddenly, you see a hand waving in front of you knocking you out of your gaze. It is =AntagonistName= “Hi Rosa, don’t you wanna see my photos of my trip with the others?”. =AntagonistName= and the rest of your classmates looks at you waiting for a response. You respond:

Option.OptionText: "I was just looking for Augusta, but that can wait."

Reaction.ReactionText: =he/she= responds “Perfect. So here I am at the beach… (blabla)”. You shut her out
=he/she= responds “Never mind, just go find Augusta.”
=he/she= responds “Well, Augusta is a loser, you should hang with us”

Option.OptionText: "Yes, I would love to"
"Well I would, if you had other photos apart from you in a bikini" (you turn around and walk towards the door)

Reaction.ReactionText: You hear her loudly laugh and say “I had no idea you were so jealous of my body“
You hear her whisper “What a bitch..”

Encounter.title: The Park
Encounter.Author: nobody
Encounter.IntroText: You just finished school and are on your way to the park in the city. Everybody from the school is coming to celebrate the beginning of a new school year. You have brought a pack of beer and some white wine, so you have enough for the whole night. =AntagonistName= is walking next to you talking about how beautiful and nice Olivia is. =He/She= seems completely obsessed with her, which you absolutely do not understand. You have known =him/her= for a long time, and =he/she= always falls way too quickly in love with girls. Maybe you should give =him/her= some advice along the way?

=AntagonistName= responds “I get a feeling that you don’t like her very much.. You should be more open towards other people”

Encounter.title: Hallway
Encounter.Author: nobody
Encounter.IntroText: It’s recess, and you’re walking down the hall. You have new clothes on, your make-up looks good, and your hair is sitting perfectly which normally never happens. It’s one of those rare good days, where you feel sexy and invincible. Down the hallway you see that Valdemar is coming your way; he looks so cool. You haven’t exchanged many words with him but you really want to catch his attention somehow. Valdemar breaks out in a big smile, and begins waving at you. You feel the rush and the excitement and you wave back at him. Suddenly, his expression changes and he looks at you a bit confused. You turn your head and notice a beautiful girl walking a few meters behind you. The rush of embarrassment starts streaming in, as you realize that he wasn’t waving at you. What should you do?

Option.OptionText: You begin laughing, and smiling, realizing how awkward this is for both of you.

Reaction.ReactionText: He smiles back at you and says "No worries, I could as well have waved at you" and continues walking over to the girl behind you.
He ignores you, and you can hear the two laughing behind your back as you walk away.

Option.OptionText: You look down at the floor and walk quickly past him without saying a word trying to hide your face.
You embrace that you made contact and say "Sorry, I thought you were waving at me"

Reaction.ReactionText: He smiles and responds "No worries, I could as well have had"
He laughs and responds "In what world" and continues over to the girl

Encounter.title: Samantha
Encounter.Author: nobody
Encounter.IntroText: It is monday and you just arrived at the school. You are walking towards the auditorium, some important politician is giving a speech at the school about how important it is to vote. All classes are invited, which makes it a bit more interesting, seeing as Valdemar is going to be there. You walk in and spot =AntagonistName= and place yourself next to =him/her=. The lecture begins and you pull out your computer to take notes. However, when you open your computer some loud noises are playing. You quickly realize that it sounds like a girl moaning, and remember that you were watching Sex and the City last night. You begin stressing, trying desperately to stop the sound, but you need to log in before. You quickly log in and shut netflix down. Stupid, stupid Samantha and all her moaning - why couldn’t she just shut up for once. You look down at your computer, completely red in the face, and feel the stares from everyone in the auditorium.. What do you do?

Option.OptionText: Whisper to =AntagonistName= “Shit, I was watching sex and the city last night”

Reaction.ReactionText: =AntagonistName= laughs and gives you a hug. Quickly after, the lecture begins and the stares decrease.
She looks at me with a smirk smile and says “this will be remembered”.

Option.OptionText: You say nothing and keep looking down

Reaction.ReactionText: The laughter and giggling in the room quickly spreads. =AntagonistName= joins in on the laughs and says nothing to you.
The laughter and giggling in the room quickly spreads. =AntagonistName= puts a hand on your shoulder and squeezes it.

Option.OptionText: You desperately look at =AntagonistName=, hoping that =he/she= can help you

Reaction.ReactionText: =AntagonistName= laughs and loudly says “Your douchback brother really likes to trick you”. She smiles at you, and the lecture continues. What a relief.

Encounter.title: Friend or flirt?
Encounter.Author: nobody
Encounter.IntroText: You are sitting in class waiting for the teacher to the come. The room is filled with chatter and noise, and the smell of lunch boxes. You open your computer and go straight to facebook checking randomly stuff to pass time. Malthe sits down next to you and you feel his stare. You smile at him, and he smiles back a bit nervous. He looks uncomfortable, which is very unlike him. His voice quivers as he says hey. You ask him ‘what’s up?’. He stutters “mmmhh. I-i-i just wanted to ask you if you maybe would want to hang out after school just the two of us?”. He looks at you with his pink cheeks and hopeful eyes waiting for a response. You have known him for many years, but you’ve never hung out just the two of you. You look a bit confused, because you’re not sure what he is proposing. What do you answer?

Option.OptionText: You lie and say that you have to hang out with Augusta, as you do not want to hurt his feelings

Reaction.ReactionText: He smiles and says "oh okay, maybe we can hang out another day"..
He responds "That is a bad excuse, but I got the message". He turns around and begins talking with the guy next to him.

He blinks and says "Okay, but I will try and change your mind"

He laughs and says "Just wait. Someday I will change your mind"

Encounter.title: The kiss
Encounter.Author: nobody
Encounter.IntroText: You’ve just arrived at the first party of the year together with your classmates. You’ve been hanging out before eating and pre-drinking together. The theme for the first party is always “Score a junior”. The idea is that if a senior and a junior makes out, they will get a prize the following school day. You think the concept is kind of stupid, but you’re drunk and having a good time. You go out on the dance floor with your friends. You feel somebody bumping into you and turn around. Valdemar is looking down at you with his beautiful blue eyes. The butterflies start filling up, as you begin dancing closer and closer with him. He leans in tries to kiss you. You want to kiss him back, but you haven’t even had a real conversation with him yet. What do you do?

Option.OptionText: Stop him, and ask him if you could go to a quiet place to get to know each other.

Reaction.ReactionText: He shakes his head, turns around and start dancing with another girl
He looks at you for a while and then he finally nods and you walk out from the dance floor together.

Encounter.title: Swimming
Encounter.Author: nobody
Encounter.IntroText: You’re having a good time at the beach and are happy that you came. Johan and some friends are playing with a ball in the ocean, and you see them waving at you, to come and join them. You slowly get up, and start taking your clothes on. You’re self conscious about being in a bikini in front of all the others. You try to suck your stomach in while walking towards the ocean. When you get in the water, you receive the ball and jump up to hit it towards Johan. He doesn’t pick the ball up but instead he’s just looking at you, while laughing. You look down, and notice your bikini top has fallen down, leaving your breasts visible. The well-known feeling of embarrassment starts streaming in. What do you do?

Option.OptionText: You quickly put it right again, and say “let’s just continue playing”

Encounter.title: Morning Meeting
Encounter.Author: nobody
Encounter.IntroText:
You’re sitting at the school’s weekly morning meeting with the other students. The principal is talking about various upcoming activities at the school in the following week. You doze away for a minute, until the party committee takes the stage with Johan at the mic. He is talking about the last party, the ‘score a junior’ party. You hear Valdemar’s name get called to come up and collect his prize - a case of beers and you feel your body starting to shake. Suddenly, a slide show begins on the projector showing photos from the party. The photos shows you and Valdemar dancing slowly and kissing. There is not just one picture but many! You feel how your face is turning red, not knowing what to do. Johan continues with the slides and finally says “And the lucky junior, who can collect a case of sodas, is ofcourse Rosa from 1.m”.
What do you do?

Option.OptionText: You exit the room through the closest door, and avoid facing the whole school!

Reaction.ReactionText: In the speakers you hear Johan saying "I guess she has fled off, too scared to claim her prize. Well well, more Sodas for me"
Johan looks around and says "Lets just move on with the program .. " and the chatter continues.

Encounter.Author: nobody
Encounter.IntroText: You’re waiting in line at the Cantina to buy some lunch. The line is long and you’re getting kind of impatient. In front of you is a really geeky guy, a bit chubby with glasses resting on his big cheeks. He is getting teased by the group of jogs in front of him. Amongst them is Valdemar, who is trying to stop the others. You hear him saying “Guys, give him back his food.” You hear one of the others saying “I am just helping him lose weight” while laughing and poking to the poor guys stomach. Valdemar steps in between them looking at the guys saying “Seriously guys, that’s enough. Just let him be”. The jogs turn around still laughing but leaving the guy alone. Valdemar turns around and your eyes meet.

Option.OptionText: You look away, pretending you didn’t hear anything
You look at the geeky guy and then back at valdemar saying “Those guys are just idiots”
You say “Why are you friends with them?”

Encounter.title: Intro: Johan 2
Encounter.Author: nobody
Encounter.IntroText: You just finished school and are on your way to the soccer pitches with Augusta. The boys’ first team are playing their first match of the season and many of the students are going down to watch the match and cheer on the team. When you arrive at the pitch you see Johan talking with his father. Johan is putting on his soccer boots, getting ready for the match. His father is talking about how he should play. You see Johan getting a bit annoyed and you hear him say “Can’t you just let me play my game, and watch from the sideline like a normal dad”. His dad shakes his head “You would never have been able to play on this team if I hadn’t pushed you”. Suddenly, Johan notices you and Augusta and he becomes silent waiting for you to go by..

Option.OptionText: You give him a smile and say “We’ll be cheering on the sidelines”
You say “Good luck, Johan” and quickly walk by
You turn your head pretending you didn’t see him
Unused option
Unused option

Encounter.title: Bus: Takeoff
Encounter.Author: nobody
Encounter.IntroText: You just arrived to the bus with your sleeping bag and pad ready for the intro trip. You’ve got your pillow with you and your wearing your most relaxing clothes to make the bus-trip as comfortable as possible. Like all other 1. year students you have go on a intro trip to a cottage house. Every class is assigned a tutor, and your class has gotten Johan from 2.Y. He’s standing at the bus flirting with Olivia. You go over to drop your bags in the trunk of the bus. Johan comes over and take your bags “You look tired, Rosa. Have you been up all night?”. You look at him a bit confused

Option.OptionText: You respond “No, I’m just not wearing any make-up”

Reaction.ReactionText: He laughs and says "I see. A word of advice, you look better with make-up" and walks away. You feel a bit angry while thinking of what an idiot he is.
He says "Argh okay, you look nice though" and gives you a crooked smile.

Option.OptionText: “Well thanks. And no. I am not tired.” you say with a hint of annoyment in your voice.

Reaction.ReactionText: He laughs while saying "Sorry, I didn't mean to offend you" and walks away
He gives you a silly look and says "Seems like your not a morning person". You roll your eyes and walk away.

Option.OptionText: You just nod and say “No. But I am tired” and you walk away not wanting to engage in a conversation with Johan

Reaction.ReactionText: You feel him looking at you a bit confused but he doesn't say anything.

Option.OptionText: Unused option
Unused option

Encounter.title: Teacher's Pet
Encounter.Author: nobody
Encounter.IntroText: You’re sitting in class having math and you’re listening to Mr. Nielsen explain something about integral calculus. He suddenly turns to you and asks you to go up to the whiteboard and solve the problem. You look around, feeling the stares of all your classmates. Thankfully you’ve done your homework, so you have no problem solving it. You quickly draw, explain and calculate the result. Mr Nielsen looks at you impressed and says to the class “This is how it’s done, good job Rosa”. On you’re way back to your seat Olivia loudly says “Someone has become the teacher’s pet” she says with a smirk smile.

Option.OptionText: You give her an evil stare

Reaction.ReactionText: Olivia laughs even more seeing how it annoys you.
Olivia becomes quiet and looks down at the table

Option.OptionText: You ignore her
You say “At least it’s better than being the teacher’s worst student”

Reaction.ReactionText: Olivia looks surprised and a bit angry. She looks down at the table not knowing what to say.
She laughs and says "Like that will ever be true!"

Encounter.title: CottageTrip part 1
Encounter.Author: nobody
Encounter.IntroText: The bus-trip went surprisingly smooth, probably because you were just talking with Augusta the whole way. You just arrived at the cottage house and have put your luggage in the rooms. Johan is explaining about the activities for today while dividing you into smaller groups; you and =AntagonistName= are in the same group. The first activity is a chain of clothes. The goal is to create the longest chain with the clothes you have on. You look at =AntagonistName= who’s already standing in =his/her= underwear. =He/She= is shouting to the others that they should take all their clothes of, to make the longest chain. You don’t feel that comfortable with taking everything off. What do you do?

Option.OptionText: You keep your pants and your shirt on

Reaction.ReactionText: =AntagonistName= looks at you and says "You're so boring, Rosa"
=AntagonistName= notice that you look uncomfortable and whispers to you "We have enough clothes, so don't worry"

Option.OptionText: You decide to just do as the others and take everything off except your underwear

Reaction.ReactionText: =AntagonistName= says "Good job, Rosa!" and places your clothes in the end of the chain
=AntagonistName= says "That was about time!" and places your clothes in the end of the chain

Option.OptionText: You refuse to participate in the activity because you feel it is stupid

Reaction.ReactionText: =AntagonistName= says "Wow. I didn't know you were so shy, Rosa" laughing to the others
=AntagonistName= looks at you and says "No worries, we have enough clothes" and gives you a big smile

Encounter.title: Valdemar asks Rosa out
Encounter.Author: nobody
Encounter.IntroText: The sun is shining, the birds are humming, and you’re in a good mood. You finished school early and just said goodbye to your classmates. While walking with your bike away from the school you hear someone running up behind you. You turn around and see Valdemar coming towards you. He smiles and says “Hi Rosa, I’m glad I just catched you” he says with a smile. He continues “I wanted to ask what you are doing Friday? And if your perhaps would want to go to a concert with me?” he looks at you intensely with his big blue eyes. You feel your heart beginning to race, as you’re trying to look for words to say.

Option.OptionText: You respond “I would love to!”

Reaction.ReactionText: He smiles while saying "Perfect! I will text you the details later! It will be fun!"
He looks relieved and says "I was hoping you would say that! I will text you the details!"

Option.OptionText: You stutter “L-like a date? ”

Reaction.ReactionText: He chuckles "Yes, like a date. I will text you the details" he says with confident and a crooked smile.

Option.OptionText: You’re quiet for a while thinking of what to say. You say “Well, I don't want to give you the wrong impression, so maybe it's not a good idea”

Reaction.ReactionText: He looks at you a bit surprised "It doesn't have to be a date. We can just go as friends. I will text you the details" he confidently says
